        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down.</hi> | Beckenham | <hi rend="print">Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Ap 13<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Many thanks for your suggestion, &amp; I have written to Turin to enquire who is the translator.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I have no idea who wrote the Times Review.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> He has no knowledge of science, &amp; seems to me a windbag full of metaphysics &amp; classics, so that I do not much regard his adverse judgment, though I suppose it will injure the sale. Should you ever hear who wrote it, be so kind as to inform me.</p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

